			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865901">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre (Optional):</strong> Horror, Other: Discovery</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout (Optional):</strong> The page will have some test logs, addendums and audio logs</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> In Antarctica a dark portal to another dimension suddenly appears, after some scientists get lost in Antarctica the foundation started an investigation. That is when they found the dark warriors. Lead by a general corrupted by darkness and the darkness is literal darkness they want the world to be dark with no light source in sight. So the goal of the Dark army is: Destroy all light in any dimension that exists, They want darkness to stay in all dimensions since darkness makes them stronger and if they are at their strongest they can rule multiple dimensions and establish several civilizations. Sort of nations, kingdoms and or empires but on a large scale</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> After the foundation finds the portal and the creatures a provisional site is built around the portal. The SCP includes three entities, the general, his soldiers (proxies) and the portal. The general commands his proxies or the proxies act on their own attacking any life-forms not &quot;Embracing the dark&quot;. The general and his proxies are dark they don't have: skin, skeletons or even organs. the general is rarely seen his soldiers are mostly in our dimension and not in the &quot;Dark&quot; dimension. Both the soldiers and the general can corrupt biological life forms by killing them but the portal only provides a mode of transportation from dimension to dimension, when a human is killed a dark goo consumes them and turns them into a soldier but if the body is too damaged or did not die by the hands of the entities no transformation will happen. All dark entities have a severe case of Photophobia<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-220771-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-220771-1')">1</a></sup> since light can hurt and melt them. Inside the portal there seems to be a world which had a SK-Class Dominance Shift Scenario where the entities took over earth in a crusade or conquest to end all life and rule over all dimensions but humans still survive in that dimension they are near extinction but they did survive. The foundation also found the general is building an army which could result in a BI Class Pre-Invasion Scenario. In which case Project L.B.L<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-220771-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-220771-2')">2</a></sup> Is to be launched</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;more</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Show&nbsp;less</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> The attention grabber here is the army. While it is obvious the army will attack the tense feeling of not knowing when and the size of the army will give interest to readers to continue reading.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> None</p>
