			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866248">
									

<p>Hello Dr Itzhak! let's take a look :)</p>
<p><strong>SAND</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>The concept:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Elevator Pitch: In Antarctica a dark portal to another dimension suddenly appears, after some scientists get lost in Antarctica the foundation started an investigation. That is when they found the dark warriors. Lead by a general corrupted by darkness.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Overall, this concept feels a bit un-engaging to me. As it stands there isn't really anything that separates this/makes it stand out from similar ideas (theres a few 'dark armies' that exist already in the media). Just having a 'dark army', with no further context won't really be able to carry the article, as it doesn't offer much to get invested in, or much to look into behind, &quot;an evil army of evil dark things will invade us, but we don't know why&quot;.</p>
<p>What exactly are they're motives?- currently their isn't really a reason for them to doing this, which makes the narrative feel a bit flat, as there doesn't seem to be any reason for the end goal. what actually is this &quot;darkness&quot;? -what role will it play in the narrative? what about the skip will make me as the reader invested?</p>
<p><strong>The narrative:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Central Narrative: After the foundation finds the portal and the creatures a provisional site is built around the portal. The SCP includes two entities, the general and his soldiers (proxies). The general commands his proxies or the proxies act on their own attacking any life-forms not &quot;Embracing the dark&quot;. The general and his proxies are dark they don't have: skin, skeletons or even organs. the general is rarely seen his soldiers are mostly in our dimension and not in the &quot;Dark&quot; dimension. Both the soldiers and the general can corrupt biological life forms by killing them, when a human is killed a dark goo consumes them and turns them into a soldier but if the body is too damaged or did not die by the hands of the entities no transformation will happen. All dark entities have a severe case of Photophobia1 since light can hurt and melt them. Inside the portal there seems to be a world which had a SK-Class Dominance Shift Scenario where the entities took over earth in that dimension but humans still survived and are near extinction. The foundation also found the general is building an army which could result in a BI Class Pre-Invasion Scenario.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As for the narrative, This starts off fine, but then seems to turn into additional info on the skip? What events take place during the narrative? how was the skip found initially? who are the characters? how are the questions raised in the concept answered? whats the payoff?- what is the narrative building up to?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Hook/Attention-Grabber: The attention grabber here is the army. It's goals are yet unknown and it's size is large and feared. I think readers would want to continue reading to know the mysterious outcome of the article.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Do note that the skip doesn't need to be dangerous to be interesting, what about the skips themselves are interesting? why should I as the reader care about the concept (or what takes place in the narrative?).</p>
<p><strong>Red or green?</strong><br />
Due to my afore mentioned concerns, no-greenlight.</p>
<p>If you would like me review this (or any concept) further, then please feel free to send me a PM or ask via IRC. Response times generally range from 2-12 hours over PMs. If your looking for additional critiques/perspectives in general, then I would highly recommend contacting the butterfly squad :)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Cheers,</p>
<p>RED</p>

